  "name": "KIM-GS Kinetic Integrity Mapping – Ground Systems",
  "alternateName": "KIM-GS",
  "description": "Protocol for mapping kinetic loads, rigging geometry, load paths, and substrate response during ground-based high-mass relocation. Defines dynamic load factors, angle tolerances, and safe movement envelopes for vaults, safes, biodensity equipment, and calibration-sensitive systems.",
